(12, 'Page', '2018-01-26 14:10:27', '2017-10-27 12:14:00', 'frequently-asked-questions', 'Frequently Asked Questions', 'FAQ', '<h3><span style=\"font-size: 1.17em;\">How does it work?</span></h3><p>Take a look at our short video: <a title=\"How Does it Work?\" href=\"[file_link,id=345]\" target=\"_blank\">How Does it Work?</a></p><p> <a href=\"[file_link,id=345]\"><img class=\"leftAlone\" style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" title=\"\" src=\"assets/Uploads/_resampled/ResizedImageWzMwMCwxOTBd/How-Does-it-Work2.JPG\" alt=\"How Does it Work2\" width=\"300\" height=\"190\"></a></p><p> </p><h3>How much does it cost?</h3><p>Review our pricing structure here: <a title=\"Pricing Structure\" href=\"[sitetree_link,id=18]\">Pricing Structure</a>.</p><p>We are sure you\'ll like it.</p><h3>What is a \'Simple Tender\'?</h3><p>For jobs that don\'t have a detailed specification document, schedule of prices or detailed drawings etc. If all you\'ve got is a photo, a description of what you want and possibly a video, then the \'Simple Tender\' is for you. We\'ve made it as easy as possible for you to upload your job and get the tender underway - and it\'s free!</p><p> </p><h3>How many photos should I upload?</h3><p>Photos are valuable for the tenderers pricing the work. Upload enough photos to clearly show all facets of the job, the surrounding environment, access points and sensitive areas (eg. your favourite tree which you don\'t want cut down). Note that we limit the size of the photos to a maximum of 2Mb each; you may need to lower the resolution of your camera to ensure the photos are below this limit.</p><p> </p><h3>Do I need to upload a sketch or plan?</h3><p>This depends entirely on the job. A tender for a job to clean a building would normally not require a sketch or plan. A tender for a tree removal would be made clearer with a sketch showing where the cut branches are to be stacked. A tender for the construction of a shed would need a clear plan and a tender for the construction of a house would need several sheets of detailed design plans.</p><p> </p><h3>Should I upload a video?</h3><p>This depends on the scale of the work. A video is valuable to communicate to the tenderers the scale of the project, describe some of the aspects of the project that are difficult to communicate in words and provide an idea of the surrounding environment. Ensure video file sizes are kept to a minimum to assist with upload and download speeds.</p><p> </p><h3>Do I need to include contract documents when I set up the tender?</h3><p>This depends on the level of complexity of the project and the value of the work. If the tender is to paint a fence then contract documents would be unlikely to be needed; the contract would be based on the detail provided in the description, the photos provided, the price and any other details provided in the Question and Answers. If the tender is to build a house then it would be usual to include a full package of documents with the tender, such as drawings, specifications, terms of payment, conditions etc.</p><p> </p><h3>What information do I need to provide when I submit my price?</h3><p>This depends on what the purchaser requires. As a minimum you will need to submit a price only. Other information that may be required by the purchaser includes clarifications and notes, schedule of prices, sketches/designs and other documents as required by the purchaser. Note that when you submit the tender you are required to confirm that you have read and understood all the information provided by the purchaser.</p><p> </p><h3>What if the price submitted differs from the schedule of prices (if submitted)?</h3><p>The total price submitted takes precedence over the schedule of prices. The purchaser and seller will have to negotiate changes to the schedule of prices so that it matches the total price.</p><p> </p><h3>When I assess the tenders do I need to accept the lowest price?</h3><p>If the tender is a simple one with no terms and conditions then you are to use your own judgement to assess which tender provides the best fit for the services you require. If the tender is more complex, with conditions of tendering as part of the tender docmentation, you are bound to assess the tenders according to the conditions of tendering.</p><p> </p><h3>What protection does Honest Day\'s Work offer buyers?</h3><p>Honest Day\'s Work provides a service to connect buyers with sellers. The buyer and seller to agree on the terms of the contract, the price and the timeframe. When the tender process is complete and the contract has been awarded Honest Day\'s Work involvement in the process is complete and the completion of the contract is then between the buyer and the seller.</p><p> </p><h3>What if circumstances out of my control, such as the weather, mean the contract is delayed?</h3><p>Each scenario will be different; it is up to the parties to consider if the circumstances are covered in the conditions of contract (if part of the contract), or if not if the circumstances represent a fair and reasonable reason for delay. If the parties can not come to an agreement then the Small Claims tribunal is an option for resolution.</p><p> </p><h3>I want to ask a tender question that contains commercially sensitive information - should I do this.</h3><p>You can ask commercially sensitive questions; if the purchaser thinks it is appropriate they will make the question and answer only viewable to you. If you are concerned that the information is highly sensitive then it is best not to disclose it.</p><p> </p><h3>What if you disagree with feedback that has been submitted against your account?</h3><p>In the case of feedback being given which you disagree with Honest Day\'s work will assess the nature of the feedback provided by both parties and make a decision regarding weather the feedback is warranted or should be modified/removed. We undertake to make a fair and consistent decision on feedback; if either party remains unhappy we can review the facts and reconsider our decision. Where disagreement remains between the buyer and the seller it may be appropriate for the parties to take the dispute to the small claims tribunal.</p><p> </p><h3>What is the difference between and Open Tender and a Closed Tender?</h3><p>An open tender is one that is visible to all users and for which tenders can be submitted by all users. A closed tender is one where the purchaser invites specific users to price the work. Invited tenders are suitable for work that is highly specialised and the potential tenderers are well known, or for work where the purchasers experience/knowledge determines that the best value for money and quality is only provided through certain tenderers. A closed tender will not appear on searches.</p><p> </p><h3>How do I pay for setting up or submitting a tender?</h3><p>There are two options. PayPal accepts all major credit cards. POLI is a system where you can log into your bank with the Honest Day\'s Work environment and make a direct debit payment. Both of these systems are secure. We do not retain credit card details; the payments are handled entirely by PayPal and POLI. POLI supports direct debits with the following banks ANZ, ASB, BankDirect, Bank of New Zealand, Kiwibank, TSB Bank and Westpac and is used by other large organisations such as NZTA, Bunnings and the Wharehouse. More information on POLI and PayPal can be found here:</p><p> </p><p><a title=\"PayPal\" href=\"https://www.paypal.com/nz/home\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"leftAlone\" style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" title=\"\" src=\"assets/Uploads/_resampled/ResizedImageWzE5OCw3OF0/Paypal.JPG\" alt=\"Paypal\" width=\"198\" height=\"78\"></a></p><p>  <a title=\"POLI\" href=\"https://www.polipay.co.nz/\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"leftAlone\" style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" title=\"\" src=\"assets/Uploads/_resampled/ResizedImageWzE5OSw4MV0/POLI.JPG\" alt=\"POLI\" width=\"199\" height=\"81\"></a></p><h3>I\'m still not sure...</h3><p>Read the information on our resources pages:</p><p><a title=\"Resources for Preparing Tenders\" href=\"[sitetree_link,id=16]\">Resources for Preparing Tenders</a></p><p><a title=\"Resources for Submitting Tenders\" href=\"[sitetree_link,id=17]\">Resources for Submitting Tenders</a></p><p> </p>', NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 13, 0, 0, NULL, 'Inherit', 'Inherit', 48, 2),
(13, 'Page', '2018-01-26 14:15:33', '2017-10-27 12:43:22', 'terms-and-conditions', 'Terms and Conditions', NULL, '<p>Terms and conditions, last updated 15 December 2017</p><p> </p><p>Honest Day\'s Work objective is to connect people who need work completed with those who need work to complete. The terms and conditions below help to keep parties on both sides of the contract aware of their rights and obligations.</p><p> </p><h2>1 Acceptance</h2><p> </p><p>1.1 By registering as a member of Honest Day\'s Work you accept these terms and conditions and will adhere to them.</p><p>1.2 Occasionally Honest Day\'s Work will amend these terms and conditions. We will advise you by email or by site notification. We will generally give you a month to review these changes. Amendments will become effective immediately once posted on the Honest Day\'s Work website. It is your responsibility to ensure you are familiar with the latest terms and conditions. Your continued use of our services will represent your agreement to the amended terms and conditions.</p><p> </p><h2>2 Membership</h2><p> </p><p>2.1 Becoming a Member: Becoming a member is free. You may only register as a member if you are resident in New Zealand or Australia (unless specifically authorised by us in writing) and can form a legally binding contract that is enforceable against you. You must be at least 18 years old. By registering as a member, you warrant that you can form a legally binding contract.</p><p>Honest Day\'s Work may, at its sole discretion, refuse the services to anyone at any time.</p><p> </p><p>2.2 Accurate Information: You warrant that you have provided complete, accurate and current personal information when registering as a member. You must maintain and update your personal information held by Honest Day\'s Work to ensure it is kept current at all times. Honest Day\'s Work may phone or mail you to verify these details. You must not register as a member under multiple identities or personas (whether false or not). However, at Honest Day\'s Work\'s discretion, you may create a business membership in addition to your personal membership.</p><p> </p><p>2.3 Termination of membership: Honest Day\'s Work reserves the right to decline to register or to terminate your membership without entering into further discussions with you. Without limiting the foregoing, Honest Day\'s Work may terminate your membership if a serious complaint or multiple complaints are received about you from other members, if you breach these terms and conditions, if you impersonate another member, or if we, at our sole discretion, deem your behaviour to be unacceptable. Members who have registered under multiple aliases will have all of their aliases disabled. When limiting your activities on the Website Honest Day\'s Work may consider offsite conduct such as prior criminal convictions, insolvency, or any other conduct that puts our community or systems at risk. In the event of termination, you also agree that you will not open or attempt to open any new Honest Day\'s Work memberships. You may at any time close your Honest Day\'s Work membership by giving us three days\' notice in writing. If you close your membership, or if it is terminated by Honest Day\'s Work, your ability to use the Honest Day\'s Work website will end.</p><p> </p><p>2.4 Security of your login information: You are responsible for keeping your login information, including your email address and password, secret and secure. Without limiting the foregoing, you agree:</p><p> </p><p>not to permit any other person to use your user name or membership; and</p><p> </p><p>not to disclose, or provide to any other person, your password, email address, date of birth or any other information in connection with your membership that may allow them to gain access to your membership.</p><p>You agree to immediately inform Honest Day\'s Work of any unauthorised use of your password or username, including that of your general user accounts and to ensure that you do not allow third parties to use your account.</p><p> </p><p>2.5 Emails and newsletters: Honest Day\'s Work will send you emails relating to your membership, transactions and other activities on the Website, and for promoting and marketing other Honest Day\'s Work products and Services to you. Honest Day\'s Work may also send regular electronic newsletters to members. Newsletters will contain clear and obvious instructions for how you can unsubscribe from the mailing list.</p><p> </p><h2>3 General</h2><p> </p><p>3.1 General</p><p> </p><p>All tenders, tender submissions or communications made through Honest Day\'s Work shall be made in good faith.</p><p> </p><p>You must not damage, interfere with or harm the Website or Services, or any network, or system underlying or connected to them, or attempt to do so.</p><p> </p><p>You may not use a robot, spider, scraper or other unauthorised automated means to access the Website or information featured on it for any purpose.</p><p> </p><p>You shall not list your email address, phone number or any other contact detail within the description of the tender, listing comments and/or questions, in your member profile, or in the Honest Day\'s Work message boards, except where expressly required by Honest Day\'s Work in the contact fields.</p><p> </p><p>You must list tenders in New Zealand dollars and include GST in all tender submissions. GST shall be clearly marked by the tenderers on any submitted tender schedules or pricing detail. All tax obligations are the responsibility of the seller and/or the buyer (as the parties determine).</p><p> </p><p>You must not complete a transaction outside of the Honest Day\'s Work process or otherwise seek to avoid Honest Day\'s Work\'s fees. Attempts by you to avoid fees, including through multiple memberships, premature tender withdrawal, or otherwise, may result in Honest Day\'s Work suspending or terminating your membership at the discretion of Honest Day\'s Work.</p><p> </p><p>You must not use the Services or the Website to promote services for sale outside the Services.</p><p> </p><p>You are responsible for any actions taken through your membership. Honest Day\'s Work memberships are not transferable and therefore cannot be sold, leased, lent or traded without specific written authorisation from Honest Day\'s Work.</p><p> </p><p>3.2 Your obligations as a Contractor/Seller</p><p> </p><p>Contractors/Sellers must be located in New Zealand or Australia. Contractors/Sellers outside of these countries are not permitted to submit tenders on Honest Day\'s Work, unless specifically authorised in writing by Honest Day\'s Work.</p><p> </p><p>You will only submit tender proposals that are accurate, current, complete, and include all relevant information about the terms of sale and payment terms. It is your responsibility to ensure that your Tender Submissions are fully compliant with the terms and conditions contained in a relevant Tender Bid and any amendments thereto from the Procuring Party. Honest Day\'s Work will not be liable in any way for your failure for any reason to comply with such terms and conditions.</p><p> </p><p>You will only submit tenders for contracts that you are legally entitled, qualified and competent to complete.</p><p> </p><p>It is your responsibility to ensure that all data uploaded to the Honest Day\'s Work website is in a standardised electronic form compatible with both Honest Day\'s Work and the buyers’ requirements. To clarify the appropriate data formats you should contact either Honest Day\'s Work or the buyer via the question and answer forum for the tender. Failure to upload data in the correct format may render your tender null and void.</p><p> </p><p>All tender submissions must comply with New Zealand law. You must not submit anything that is illegal, offensive (including anything of a defamatory, pornographic, or racially or ethnically objectionable nature), or unsafe, or any proposal of which the transaction is prohibited by, or violates any, law. You are responsible for ensuring that any tender submitted by you does not breach this clause 4.2(f). You agree that Honest Day\'s Work may disclose your personal information, including your name and contact details, to the relevant authorities, parties and/or the applicable intellectual property right holders (or their representatives) if we consider that you are in breach of this clause at any time.</p><p> </p><p>You must ensure you hold the copyright or are otherwise licensed to use any images you add to your tender submissions.</p><p> </p><p>Your tender submission may only contain a URL for a website that contains further information on the submission you have listed. This website must not offer any services for sale, or contain contact details. You must not use Honest Day\'s Work tender listings to promote a business or website.</p><p> </p><p>You must not manipulate tenders through shill-bidding or assuming multiple roles in a single transaction.</p><p> </p><p>Your submitted tender and submitted price is not retractable once the tender has closed. You must only submit a tender if you intend to commit to the contract should you be selected as the winning tenderer.</p><p>If you are notified that your tender submission has been successful, you must complete the transaction in the manner specified. By making a tender submission you warrant and represent that you have the legal right to enter into and complete the transaction.</p><p> </p><p>You agree to your email address and name being provided to the buyer when the tender closes.</p><p> </p><p>It is the buyer’s responsibility to notify winning tenderers.</p><p> </p><p>If you are selected as the winning tenderer You must promptly begin the contract for the buyer or as may be otherwise described in the contract agreement.</p><p> </p><p>You agree to your username and the amount of your winning tender being publicly shown on the Honest Day\'s Work Website.</p><p> </p><p>If you are selected as the winning tenderer but do not complete the contract, you will receive a warning from Honest Day\'s Work if the seller complains about you. After 3 such complaints, Honest Day\'s Work may suspend or terminate your membership.</p><p> </p><p>3.3 Your obligations as a Purchaser/Client</p><p> </p><p>You must be located in New Zealand or Australia to list tenders on Honest Day\'s Work. People outside of these countries are not permitted to create tenders on Honest Day\'s Work.</p><p> </p><p>Tenders are not pre-screened for content. Honest Day\'s Work reserves the right to remove any tender that it deems unsuitable or in breach of the terms and conditions.</p><p> </p><p>When you create a tender on Honest Day\'s Work, you should do so with the intention of awarding this contract through the site. Therefore you should not advertise your proposal through another forum. If you remove a tender you may incur a non-refundable withdrawal fee, regardless of the reason.</p><p> </p><p>You agree to your email address being provided to the tenderers when your tender closes.</p><p> </p><p>You must make full and prompt payment for any service/contract you buy, or as may be otherwise described in the contract agreement.</p><p> </p><p>If you do not pay for the contract as required by the contract documents or the contract agreement, you will receive a warning from Honest Day\'s Work if the seller complains about you. After 3 such complaints, Honest Day\'s Work may suspend or terminate your membership.</p><p> </p><p>3.4 Feedback</p><p> </p><p>Feedback is provided for the purpose of facilitating trading between members on the Honest Day\'s Work Website. Feedback you provide on other members must not contain offensive, defamatory, retaliatory or inappropriate language or content. Honest Day\'s Work may remove any feedback that we consider to be offensive, defamatory, retaliatory or inappropriate.</p><p> </p><p>You may only give member feedback that relates to a specific contract or tender. You must not post feedback on a contract or tender that does not relate to that specific contract or tender.</p><p> </p><p>You must not post feedback about yourself or include any contact details or personal information in your feedback.</p><p> </p><h2>4 Fair and Honest Representation</h2><p> </p><p>4.1 The Services: Honest Day\'s Work provides a venue to introduce members who want to negotiate contracts. Honest Day\'s Work does not take any part in the purchase or sale of services, products or contracts other than by providing our Website as a venue for members. If a contract is accepted by a purchaser, a contract will be formed between the purchaser and the seller directly. We do not act as agent for either party and do not participate in any purchase, sale or transaction between you and other members.</p><p> </p><p>4.2 At your own risk: Transactions and all other contact between you and other members are conducted entirely at your own risk. You agree that Honest Day\'s Work takes no responsibility or liability for any misconduct of any of its members including,  members that have registered under false pretences or who attempt to defraud you. Honest Day\'s Work gives no undertakings, representations, or warranties in relation to contracts tendered, listed or awarded on the Website including:</p><ul><li>the content, safety, description, worthiness, quality, or legality of the contracts or services that are procured on the Website;</li>\n<li>the accuracy or truth of tender details;</li>\n<li>that any tender submitted or awarded will meet your requirements or expectations; or</li>\n<li>about the ability of members to complete a transaction.</li>\n</ul><p> </p><p>4.3 Disclaimer: You understand and agree that:</p><p> </p><p>Your use of the Services is at your sole risk. The Website and Services are provided on an \"as is\" and \"as available\" basis. To the maximum extent permitted by law.</p><p> </p><p>Honest Day\'s Work disclaims and excludes liability for any guarantees that a contract will be carried out with reasonable care and skill, fitness for a particular purpose, time of completion or price for the contract;</p><p> </p><p>Honest Day\'s Work does not warrant that i) the Services provided will be uninterrupted, timely, secure, or error free, or ii) that any information (including feedback) provided on the Website is error-free or reliable;</p><p> </p><p>No advice or information that is obtained by you from Honest Day\'s Work or anyone else shall create any warranty by Honest Day\'s Work that is not expressly stated in the terms and conditions; and</p><p> </p><p>Responsibility for the content of advertisements appearing on this Website (including hyperlinks to advertisers\' own websites) rests solely with the advertisers. The placement of such advertisements on the Website does not constitute Honest Day\'s Work\'s recommendation or endorsement of the advertised product or service. Each advertiser is solely responsible for any representation made in connection with its advertisement.</p><p> </p><p>While Honest Day\'s Work may facilitate payment for some items by credit card, Honest Day\'s Work is in no way involved in the Contract transaction itself, and responsibility for any refund rests with the seller.</p><p> </p><p>While Honest Day\'s Work has systems in place to reduce the risk of credit card fraud, Honest Day\'s Work is not responsible for protecting members from credit card fraud. Honest Day\'s Work\'s fraud protection systems may from time to time block legitimate credit card payments. In these cases payment will need to be made by other means.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>4.4 Liability: To the maximum extent permitted by law, any and all liability and responsibility of Honest Day\'s Work to you or any other person under or in connection with these terms and conditions, or in connection with the services, this Website, another Member\'s acts or omissions, or your use of or inability to use, the services or this Website, is excluded regardless of whether such liability arises in contract, tort (including negligence), equity, breach of statutory duty or otherwise. Honest Day\'s Work\'s liability and responsibility is excluded in respect of any and all loss or damage, whether direct or indirect, including, without limitation, loss of profits, loss of data, loss of business or anticipated savings, general and special damages, and consequential and incidental loss.</p><p> </p><p>4.5 Indemnity: You agree to release, indemnify and keep indemnified us from and against all actions, claims, costs (including legal costs and expenses), losses, proceedings, damages, liabilities, or demands suffered or incurred by us to any person arising out of or in connection with your failure to comply with these terms and conditions, your failure to complete a transaction, your use of Honest Day\'s Work\'s message boards, your contract or attempted sale of services prohibited under clause 4.2(f).</p><p> </p><p>4.6 Breach: Without limiting any other rights and remedies available to Honest Day\'s Work, Honest Day\'s Work may limit your activities on the Website, remove your tenders, listings or other content, warn other members of your actions, issue a warning to you, suspend or terminate your membership, or refuse to provide our Services to you if you breach these terms and conditions, or where Honest Day\'s Work considers it appropriate.</p><p> </p><h2>5 Fees</h2><p> </p><p>The Honest Day\'s Work\'s current fees, which are charged for the use of the Website, are listed on our fees page in the FAQ section. Fees may be changed at any time and will be listed in the FAQ section. All fees are GST inclusive and listed in New Zealand dollars. You should review the fees prior to using our service. The non-payment of fees will result in Tenders not being listed (for Purchasers) or Tender Submissions not being submitted (for Sellers).</p><p> </p><h2>6 General</h2><p> </p><p>6.1 Website Availability: Honest Day\'s Work will use its reasonable endeavours to ensure the availability of the Website and Services, subject to any downtime required for maintenance. However, Honest Day\'s Work takes no responsibility for any system unavailability, or for any loss that is incurred as a result of Website or Services being unavailable. Further, Honest Day\'s Work assumes no responsibility for the corruption of any data or information held by Honest Day\'s Work and holds no liability for any lack of performance due to causes outside the control of Honest Day’s Work.</p><p> </p><p>6.2 Disputes: As Honest Day\'s Work is not a party to any sale or transaction between you and another member, you agree not to involve, or attempt to involve, Honest Day\'s Work in any dispute or in the resolution of disputes that arise between you and another member as a result of the Services provided. If you wish to take Proceedings against another member, you can contact Honest Day\'s Work for a statutory declaration form, which must be completed before we will consider releasing anyone else\'s information to you. You may only request contact details for the sole purpose of making a claim.</p><p> </p><p>6.3 Intellectual Property Rights: Honest Day\'s Work owns all proprietary and intellectual property rights in the Website (including text, graphics, logos, icons and sound recordings) and the software and other material underlying and forming part of the Services and the Website.</p><p> </p><p>6.4 Entire agreement: These terms and conditions supersede all previous conditions, understandings, commitments, agreements and representations whatsoever whether oral or written, and constitutes the entire agreement, between the parties, relating to the subject matter of these terms and conditions.</p><p> </p><h2>7 Terminology</h2><p>\'Tender\' includes both \'open tenders\' and \'closed tenders\' and refers to a listing on the website which you purchase, negotiate, offer, buy, sell or advertise any service or product or contract to perform work or request work;</p><p>\'Open tender\' refers to a tender which any member of Honest Day\'s Work may submit a proposal;</p><p>\'Closed tender\' refers to a tender which only members of Honest Day\'s Work who have been invited by the Client may submit submissions;</p><p>‘Client or Purchaser’ refers to the registered member who has listed a tender on Honest Day’s Work.</p><p>‘Contractor or Seller’ refers to the registered member who has submitted a Proposal on Honest Day’s Work.</p><p>‘Proposal’ refers to an offer to complete a service or provide a product or complete a job for a sum of money.</p><p>\'Tender submission\' refers to offers from sellers to complete the work as described in the tender documentation, including the tender notices during the tender period;</p><p>\'Contract\' refers to the agreement between the buyer and the selected tenderer to have the work completed to the agreed standard and extent and timeframe for the agreed cost.</p><p>\'Member\' means a registered user of Honest Day\'s Work;</p><p>\'Services\' means any one or more of the services offered by Honest Day\'s Work Limited, including online tenders, classifieds, and any other service that Honest Day\'s Work may offer;</p><p>\'Website\' means any Honest Day\'s Work website through which the services are offered;</p><p> </p><h2>8 Law</h2><p>These terms and conditions are governed by the laws of New Zealand. You submit to the non-exclusive jurisdiction of the Courts of New Zealand.</p>', NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 13, 0, 0, NULL, 'Inherit', 'Inherit', 14, 2),
