icular, your obligations under Clause 4, or where Honest Day\'s Work considers it appropriate.</p><p> </p><p>2.7 Additional rules: In addition to the terms and conditions set out in this document, the Ping terms and conditions, the Afterpay terms for Honest Day\'s Work sellers, the Banned and Restricted Items list, Listing Policies, Job Listing Policies, Message Board Policy, Buyer Protection Policy and Member Services Category Policy form part of these terms and conditions.</p><p> </p><p>BECOMING A MEMBER</p><p> </p><p>3.1 Becoming a Member: Becoming a member is free. You may only register as a member if you are resident in New Zealand or Australia (unless specifically authorised by us in writing) and can form a legally binding contract that is enforceable against you. You must be at least 18 years old. By registering as a member, you warrant that you can form a legally binding contract.</p><p>Honest Day\'s Work may, at it\'s sole discretion, refuse the services to anyone at any time.</p><p> </p><p>3.2 Accurate Information: You warrant that you have provided complete, accurate and current personal information when registering as a member. You must maintain and update your personal information held by Honest Day\'s Work to ensure it is kept current at all times. Honest Day\'s Work may phone or mail you to verify these details. You must not register as a member under multiple identities or personas (whether false or not). However, at Honest Day\'s Work\'s discretion, you may create a business membership in addition to your personal membership.</p><p> </p><p>3.3 Termination of membership: Honest Day\'s Work reserves the right to decline to register or to terminate your membership without entering into further discussions with you. Without limiting the foregoing, Honest Day\'s Work may terminate your membership if a serious complaint or multiple complaints are received about you from other members, if you breach these terms and conditions, if you impersonate another member, or if we, at our sole discretion, deem your behaviour to be unacceptable. Members who have registered under multiple aliases will have all of their aliases disabled. When limiting your activities on the Website Honest Day\'s Work may consider offsite conduct such as prior criminal convictions, insolvency, or any other conduct that puts our community or systems at risk. In the event of termination, you also agree that you will not open or attempt to open any new Honest Day\'s Work memberships. You may at any time close your Honest Day\'s Work membership by giving us three days\' notice in writing. If you close your membership, or if it is terminated by Honest Day\'s Work, your ability to use the Honest Day\'s Work website will end. To the extent that you continue to access the site, clauses 2.2-2.5, 4.1 and 6.8 of these terms continue to apply.</p><p> </p><p>3.4 Security of your login information: You are responsible for keeping your login information, including your email address and password, secret and secure. Without limiting the foregoing, you agree:</p><p> </p><p>not to permit any other person to use your user name or membership; and</p><p> </p><p>not to disclose, or provide to any other person, your password, email address, date of birth or any other information in connection with your membership that may allow them to gain access to your membership.</p><p>You agree to immediatly inform Honest Day\'s Work of any unauthroised use of your password or username, including that of your general user accounts and to ensure that you do not allow thrid parties to use your account.</p><p> </p><p>3.5 Emails and newsletters: Honest Day\'s Work will send you emails relating to your membership, transactions and other activities on the Website, and for promoting and marketing other Honest Day\'s Work products and Services to you. Honest Day\'s Work may also send regular electronic newsletters to members. Newsletters will contain clear and obvious instructions for how you can unsubscribe from the mailing list.</p><p> </p><p>GENERAL RULES</p><p> </p><p>4.1 General</p><p> </p><p>All tenders, tender submissions or communications made through Honest Day\'s Work shall be made in good faith.</p><p> </p><p>You must not damage, interfere with or harm the Website or Services, or any network, or system underlying or connected to them, or attempt to do so.</p><p> </p><p>You may not use a robot, spider, scraper or other unauthorised automated means to access the Website or information featured on it for any purpose.</p><p> </p><p>You shall not list your email address, phone number or any other contact detail within the description of the tender, listing comments and/or questions, in your member profile, or in the Honest Day\'s Work message boards, except where expressly required by Honest Day\'s Work in the contact fields.</p><p> </p><p>You must list tenders in New Zealand dollars and include GST in all tender submissions. GST shall be clearly marked by the tenderers on any submitted tender schedules or pricing detail. All tax obligations are the responsibility of the seller and/or the buyer (as the parties determine).</p><p> </p><p>You must not complete a transaction outside of the Honest Day\'s Work process or otherwise seek to avoid Honest Day\'s Work\'s success fees. Attempts by you to avoid fees, including through multiple memberships, premature tender withdrawal, or otherwise, may result in Honest Day\'s Work suspending or terminating your membership at the discretion of Honest Day\'s Work.</p><p> </p><p>You must not use the Services or the Website to promote services for sale outside the Services.</p><p> </p><p>You are responsible for any actions taken through your membership. Honest Day\'s Work memberships are not transferable and therefore cannot be sold, leased, lent or traded without specific written authorisation from Honest Day\'s Work.</p><p> </p><p>4.2 Your obligations as a seller</p><p> </p><p>Sellers must be located in New Zealand or Australia. Sellers outside of these countries are not permitted to sell on Honest Day\'s Work, unless specifically authorised in writing by Honest Day\'s Work.</p><p> </p><p>You will only submit tender proposals that are accurate, current, complete, and include all relevant information about the terms of sale and payment terms. It is your responsibility to ensure that your Tender Submissions are fully compliant with the terms and conditions contained in a relevant Tender Bid and any amendments thereto from the Procuring Party. Honest Day\'s Work will not be liable in any way for your failure for any reason to comply with such terms and conditions.</p><p> </p><p>You will only submit tenders for contracts that you are legally entitled, qualified and compentent to complete.</p><p> </p><p>It is your resonsibility to ensure that all data uploaded to the Honest Day\'s Work website is in a standardised electronic form compatable with both Honest Day\'s Work and the buyers requirements. To clarify the appropriate data formats you should contact either Honest Day\'s Work or the buyer via the question and answer forum for the tender. Failure to upload data in the correct format may render your tender null and void.</p><p> </p><p>All tender submissions must comply with New Zealand law. You must not submit anything that is illegal, offensive (including anything of a defamatory, pornographic, or racially or ethnically objectionable nature), or unsafe, or any proposal of which the transaction is prohibited by, or violates any, law. You are responsible for ensuring that any tender submitted by you does not breach this clause 4.2(f). You agree that Honest Day\'s Work may disclose your personal information, including your name and contact details, to the relevant authorities, parties and/or the applicable intellectual property right holders (or their representatives) if we consider that you are in breach of this clause 4.2(f) at any time.</p><p> </p><p>You must ensure you hold the copyright or are otherwise licensed to use any images you add to your tender submissions.</p><p> </p><p>When you submit your tender on Honest Day\'s Work, you should do so with the intention of being awarded this contract through the site. Therefore you should not advertise your proposal through another forum. If you remove a tender submission for an auction you will incur a non-refundable withdrawal fee, regardless of the reason.</p><p> </p><p>Your tender submission may only contain a URL for a website that contains further information on the submission you have listed. This website must not offer any services for sale, or contain contact details. You must not use Honest Day\'s Work listings to promote a business or website.</p><p> </p><p>You must not manipulate tenders through shill-bidding or assuming multiple roles in a single transaction.</p><p> </p><p>Your submitted tender and submitted price is not retractable once the tender has closed. You must only submit a tender if you intend to commit to the contract should you be selected as the winning tenderer.</p><p>If you are notified that your tender submission has been successful, you must complete the transaction in the manner specified. By making a tender submission you warrant and represent that you have the legal right to enter into and complete the transaction.</p><p> </p><p>You agree to your email address being provided to the buyer when the tender closes.</p><p> </p><p>It is the buyers responsibility to notify winning tenderers.</p><p> </p><p>If you are selecgted as the winning tenderer You must promptly begin the contract for the buyer or as may be otherwise described in the contract agreement.</p><p> </p><p>You agree to your username and the amount of your winning tender being publicly shown on the Honest Day\'s Work Website.</p><p> </p><p>If you are selected as the winning tenderer but do not complete the contract, you will receive a warning from Honest Day\'s Work if the seller complains about 