w Zealand or Australia. Sellers outside of these countries are not permitted to sell on Honest Day\'s Work, unless specifically authorised in writing by Honest Day\'s Work.</p><p> </p><p>You will only submit tender proposals that are accurate, current, complete, and include all relevant information about the terms of sale and payment terms. It is your responsibility to ensure that your Tender Submissions are fully compliant with the terms and conditions contained in a relevant Tender Bid and any amendments thereto from the Procuring Party. Honest Day\'s Work will not be liable in any way for your failure for any reason to comply with such terms and conditions.</p><p> </p><p>You will only submit tenders for contracts that you are legally entitled, qualified and compentent to complete.</p><p> </p><p>It is your resonsibility to ensure that all data uploaded to the Honest Day\'s Work website is in a standardised electronic form compatable with both Honest Day\'s Work and the buyers requirements. To clarify the appropriate data formats you should contact either Honest Day\'s Work or the buyer via the question and answer forum for the tender. Failure to upload data in the correct format may render your tender null and void.</p><p> </p><p>All tender submissions must comply with New Zealand law. You must not submit anything that is illegal, offensive (including anything of a defamatory, pornographic, or racially or ethnically objectionable nature), or unsafe, or any proposal of which the transaction is prohibited by, or violates any, law. You are responsible for ensuring that any tender submitted by you does not breach this clause 4.2(f). You agree that Honest Day\'s Work may disclose your personal information, including your name and contact details, to the relevant authorities, parties and/or the applicable intellectual property right holders (or their representatives) if we consider that you are in breach of this clause 4.2(f) at any time.</p><p> </p><p>You must ensure you hold the copyright or are otherwise licensed to use any images you add to your tender submissions.</p><p> </p><p>When you submit your tender on Honest Day\'s Work, you should do so with the intention of being awarded this contract through the site. Therefore you should not advertise your proposal through another forum. If you remove a tender submission for an auction you will incur a non-refundable withdrawal fee, regardless of the reason.</p><p> </p><p>Your tender submission may only contain a URL for a website that contains further information on the submission you have listed. This website must not offer any services for sale, or contain contact details. You must not use Honest Day\'s Work listings to promote a business or website.</p><p> </p><p>You must not manipulate tenders through shill-bidding or assuming multiple roles in a single transaction.</p><p> </p><p>Your submitted tender and submitted price is not retractable once the tender has closed. You must only submit a tender if you intend to commit to the contract should you be selected as the winning tenderer.</p><p>If you are notified that your tender submission has been successful, you must complete the transaction in the manner specified. By making a tender submission you warrant and represent that you have the legal right to enter into and complete the transaction.</p><p> </p><p>You agree to your email address being provided to the buyer when the tender closes.</p><p> </p><p>It is the buyers responsibility to notify winning tenderers.</p><p> </p><p>If you are selecgted as the winning tenderer You must promptly begin the contract for the buyer or as may be otherwise described in the contract agreement.</p><p> </p><p>You agree to your username and the amount of your winning tender being publicly shown on the Honest Day\'s Work Website.</p><p> </p><p>If you are selected as the winning tenderer but do not complete the contract, you will receive a warning from Honest Day\'s Work if the seller complains about you. After 3 such complaints, Honest Day\'s Work may suspend or terminate your membership.</p><p> </p><p>4.3 Your obligations as a buyer</p><p> </p><p>You must be located in New Zealand or Australia to buy on Honest Day\'s Work. People outside of these countries are not permitted to create tenders on Honest Day\'s Work.</p><p> </p><p>Tenders are not pre-screened for content. Honest Day\'s Work reserves the right to remove any tender that it deems unsuitable or in breach of the terms and conditions.</p><p> </p><p>You agree to your email address being provided to the tenderers when your tender closes.</p><p> </p><p>You must make full and prompt payment for any item you buy, or as may be otherwise described in the contract agreement.</p><p> </p><p>If you do not pay for the contract as requried by the contract documents or the contract agreement, you will receive a warning from Honest Day\'s Work if the seller complains about you. After 3 such complaints, Honest Day\'s Work may suspend or terminate your membership.</p><p> </p><p>4.4 Feedback</p><p> </p><p>Feedback is provided for the purpose of facilitating trading between members on the Honest Day\'s Work Website. Feedback you provide on other members must not contain offensive, defamatory, retaliatory or inappropriate language or content. Honest Day\'s Work may remove any feedback that we consider to be offensive, defamatory, retaliatory or inappropriate.</p><p> </p><p>You may only give member feedback that relates to a specific transaction. You must not post feedback on a transaction that does not relate to that specific transaction.</p><p> </p><p>You must not post feedback about yourself or include any contact details or personal information in your feedback.</p><p> </p><p>FEES AND ACCOUNTS</p><p> </p><p>5.1 Honest Day\'s Work Listing Fees and Success Fees</p><p> </p><p>Honest Day\'s Work charges fees for the use of the Website as a venue.</p><p> </p><p>Honest Day\'s Work\'s current fees are listed on our fees page in the FAQ section.</p><p> </p><p>Any non-commission listing fees are charged at the time of listing and are not refundable.</p><p> </p><p>Honest Day\'s Work reserves the right to change the fees charged for any of our Services at any time. In the event that we introduce a new Service, the fees for that Service are effective at the launch of the Service, unless otherwise stated.</p><p> </p><p>If you are a New Zealand resident, then all fees are inclusive of GST and in New Zealand dollars unless otherwise stated. If you are not a New Zealand resident, then all fees are, unless otherwise stated, in New Zealand dollars and do not include GST. Unless otherwise stated in these terms and conditions, no interest or other financial charges will be applied to Honest Day\'s Work account balances.</p><p> </p><p>Honest Day\'s Work reserves the right to investigate queries regarding the refund of success fees with bidders, other members and any other relevant party.</p><p> </p><p>Before listing a tender, you should review Honest Day\'s Work\'s fees to ensure you are aware of the fees that you will incur.</p><p> </p><p>You must pay the fees immediately upon demand by Honest Day\'s Work.</p><p> </p><p>GENERAL PROVISIONS</p><p> </p><p>6.1 System Integrity: Honest Day\'s Work will use its reasonable endeavours to ensure the availability of the Website and Services, subject to any downtime required for maintenance. However, Honest Day\'s Work takes no responsibility for any system unavailability, or for any loss that is incurred as a result of Website or Services being unavailable. Further, Honest Day\'s Work assumes no responsibility for the corruption of any data or information held by Honest Day\'s Work.</p><p> </p><p>6.2 Resolution of disputes: As Honest Day\'s Work is not a party to any sale or transaction between you and another member, you agree not to involve, or attempt to involve, Honest Day\'s Work in any dispute or in the resolution of disputes that arise between you 