(94, 17, 4, 1, 2, 2, 'Page', '2017-11-10 14:20:45', '2017-11-10 14:08:39', 'resources-for-submitting-tenders', 'Resources for Submitting Tenders', NULL, '<p>This material is provided to give guidance on common tendering practices in New Zealand. If you are preparing a tender, read the information below. If you are submitting a tender, click <a title=\"Resources for Preparing Tenders\" href=\"[sitetree_link,id=16]\">here</a>.</p><p> </p><p>The key to submitting a competitive tender is to understand  the clients needs. The client may not select the lowest price if it is evident that that tenderer did not understand critical elements of the job. Use the forum in the tender to ask the client questions about the job, particularly if you can see risks or it is evident the client is unsure about the job.</p><p> </p><p>Each tender will require different supporting information, check well in advance of the tender close date what is required to be submitted and ensure you have enough time to prepare the documentation. If the client hasn\'t provided enough time to prepare the necessary documentation, ask them why - it may be that they don\'t understand how much time you need to prepare the submission and they may choose to extend the submission date.</p>', NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 16, 0, 0, NULL, 'Inherit', 'Inherit', 0),
(95, 17, 5, 1, 2, 2, 'Page', '2017-11-10 14:21:20', '2017-11-10 14:08:39', 'resources-for-submitting-tenders', 'Resources for Submitting Tenders', NULL, '<p>This material is provided to give guidance on common tendering practices in New Zealand. If you are preparing a tender, read the information below. If you are preparing a tender, click <a title=\"Resources for Preparing Tenders\" href=\"[sitetree_link,id=16]\">here</a>.</p><p> </p><p>The key to submitting a competitive tender is to understand  the clients needs. The client may not select the lowest price if it is evident that that tenderer did not understand critical elements of the job. Use the forum in the tender to ask the client questions about the job, particularly if you can see risks or it is evident the client is unsure about the job.</p><p> </p><p>Each tender will require different supporting information, check well in advance of the tender close date what is required to be submitted and ensure you have enough time to prepare the documentation. If the client hasn\'t provided enough time to prepare the necessary documentation, ask them why - it may be that they don\'t understand how much time you need to prepare the submission and they may choose to extend the submission date.</p>', NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 16, 0, 0, NULL, 'Inherit', 'Inherit', 0),
