umstances represent a fair and reasonable reason for delay. If the parties can not come to an agreement then the Small Claims tribunal is an option for resolution.</p><p> </p><h3>I want to ask a tender question that contains commercially sensitive information - should I do this.</h3><p>You can ask commercially sensitive questions; if the purchaser thinks it is appropriate they will make the question and answer only viewable to you. If you are concerned that the information is highly sensitive then it is best not to disclose it.</p><p> </p><h3>What if you disagree with feedback that has been submitted against your account?</h3><p>In the case of feedback being given which you disagree with Honest Day\'s work will assess the nature of the feedback provided by both parties and make a decision regarding weather the feedback is warranted or should be modified/removed. We undertake to make a fair and consistent decision on feedback; if either party remains unhappy we can review the facts and reconsider our decision. Where disagreement remains between the buyer and the seller it may be appropriate for the parties to take the dispute to the small claims tribunal.</p><p> </p><h3>What is the difference between and Open Tender and a Closed Tender?</h3><p>An open tender is one that is visible to all users and for which tenders can be submitted by all users. A closed tender is one where the purchaser invites specific users to price the work. Invited tenders are suitable for work that is highly specialised and the potential tenderers are well known, or for work where the purchasers experience/knowledge determines that the best value for money and quality is only provided through certain tenderers. A closed tender will not appear on searches.</p><p> </p><h3>How do I pay for setting up or submitting a tender?</h3><p>There are two options. PayPal accepts all major credit cards. POLI is a system where you can log into your bank with the Honest Day\'s Work environment and make a direct debit payment. Both of these systems are secure. We do not retain credit card details; the payments are handled entirely by PayPal and POLI. POLI supports direct debits with the following banks ANZ, ASB, BankDirect, Bank of New Zealand, Kiwibank, TSB Bank and Westpac and is used by other large organisations such as NZTA, Bunnings and the Wharehouse. More information on POLI and PayPal can be found here:</p><p><a href=\"https://www.polipay.co.nz/\">https://www.polipay.co.nz/</a></p><p><a href=\"https://www.paypal.com/nz/home\">https://www.paypal.com/nz/home</a></p><p> </p><h3>I\'m still not sure...</h3><p>Read the information on our resources pages:</p><p><a title=\"Resources for Preparing Tenders\" href=\"[sitetree_link,id=16]\">Resources for Preparing Tenders</a></p><p><a title=\"Resources for Submitting Tenders\" href=\"[sitetree_link,id=17]\">Resources for Submitting Tenders</a></p><p> </p>', NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 12, 0, 0, NULL, 'Inherit', 'Inherit', 0),
(108, 2, 13, 1, 2, 2, 'Page', '2017-11-10 15:49:08', '2017-09-25 06:18:29', 'about', 'About', NULL, '<p>Our mission here at Honest Day\'s Work is to provide you the opportunities you need to create your own lifestyle. In essence this means creating an open market where people can use the skills they have to find the work they want. Jump off the 9 to 5 treadmill and contract your skills out!</p><p> </p><p>We also aim to make it easier to get work done. Got 10 jobs to do, but haven\'t got the time to be ringing around chasing prices? Honest Day\'s Work provides a simple and powerful platform for you to present your jobs to the people with the right skills for the work.</p><p> </p><p><a title=\"Frequently Asked Questions\" href=\"[sitetree_link,id=12]\">FAQ\'s</a></p><p><a href=\"[sitetree_link,id=3]\">Feedback</a></p><p><a title=\"Resources for Preparing Tenders\" href=\"[sitetree_link,id=16]\">Resources for Preparing Tenders</a></p><p><a title=\"Resources for Submitting Tenders\" href=\"[sitetree_link,id=17]\">Resources for Submitting Tenders</a></p><p> </p><p><a href=\"[sitetree_link,id=13]\">Terms and Conditions</a></p>', NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 4, 0, 0, NULL, 'Inherit', 'Inherit', 0),
