sider our decision. Where disagreement remains between the buyer and the seller it may be appropriate for the parties to take the dispute to the small claims tribunal.</p><p> </p><h3>What is the difference between and Open Tender and a Closed Tender?</h3><p>An open tender is one that is visible to all users and for which tenders can be submitted by all users. A closed tender is one where the purchaser invites specific users to price the work. Invited tenders are suitable for work that is highly specialised and the potential tenderers are well known, or for work where the purchasers experience/knowledge determines that the best value for money and quality is only provided through certain tenderers. A closed tender will not appear on searches.</p><p> </p><h3>How do I pay for setting up or submitting a tender?</h3><p>There are two options. PayPal accepts all major credit cards. POLI is a system where you can log into your bank with the Honest Day\'s Work environment and make a direct debit payment. Both of these systems are secure. We do not retain credit card details; the payments are handled entirely by PayPal and POLI. POLI supports direct debits with the following banks ANZ, ASB, BankDirect, Bank of New Zealand, Kiwibank, TSB Bank and Westpac and is used by other large organisations such as NZTA, Bunnings and the Wharehouse. More information on POLI and PayPal can be found here:</p><p><a href=\"https://www.polipay.co.nz/\">https://www.polipay.co.nz/</a></p><p><a href=\"https://www.paypal.com/nz/home\">https://www.paypal.com/nz/home</a></p><p> </p><h3>I\'m still not sure...</h3><p>Read the information on our resources pages:</p><p><a title=\"Resources for Preparing Tenders\" href=\"[sitetree_link,id=16]\">Resources for Preparing Tenders</a></p><p><a title=\"Resources for Submitting Tenders\" href=\"[sitetree_link,id=17]\">Resources for Submitting Tenders</a></p><p> </p>', NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 13, 0, 0, NULL, 'Inherit', 'Inherit', 0),
