(205, 12, 38, 0, 2, 0, 'Page', '2017-12-01 16:24:35', '2017-10-27 12:14:00', 'frequently-asked-questions', 'Frequently Asked Questions', 'FAQ', '<p> </p><h3>How much does it cost?</h3><p>Review our pricing structure here: <a title=\"Pricing Structure\" href=\"[sitetree_link,id=18]\">Pricing Structure</a>.</p><p>We are sure you\'ll like it.</p><p> </p><h3>How much does it work?</h3><p>Take a look at our short video: <a title=\"How Does it Work?\" href=\"[file_link,id=345]\" target=\"_blank\">How Does it Work?</a></p><p> <a href=\"[file_link,id=345]\"><img width=\"300\" height=\"190\" title=\"\" class=\"leftAlone\" style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" alt=\"How Does it Work2\" src=\"assets/Uploads/_resampled/ResizedImageWzMwMCwxOTBd/How-Does-it-Work2.JPG\"></a></p><p> </p><h3>What is a \'Simple Tender\'?</h3><p>For jobs that don\'t have a detailed specification document, schedule of prices or detailed drawings etc. If all you\'ve got is a photo, a description of what you want and possibly a video, then the \'Simple Tender\' is for you. We\'ve made it as easy as possible for you to upload your job and get the tender underway - and it\'s free!</p><p> </p><h3>How many photos should I upload?</h3><p>Photos are valuable for the tenderers pricing the work. Upload enough photos to clearly show all facets of the job, the surrounding environment, access points and sensitive areas (eg. your favourite tree which you don\'t want cut down). Note that we limit the size of the photos to a maximum of 2Mb each; you may need to lower the resolution of your camera to ensure the photos are below this limit.</p><p> </p><h3>Do I need to upload a sketch or plan?</h3><p>This depends entirely on the job. A tender for a job to clean a building would normally not require a sketch or plan. A tender for a tree removal would be made clearer with a sketch showing where the cut branches are to be stacked. A tender for the construction of a shed would need a clear plan and