(218, 13, 10, 0, 2, 0, 'Page', '2017-12-15 16:56:38', '2017-10-27 12:43:22', 'terms-and-conditions', 'Terms and Conditions', NULL, '<p>Terms and conditions, last updated 15 December 2017</p><p> </p><p>Honest Day\'s Work objective is to connect people who need work completed with those who need work to complete. The terms and conditions below help to keep parties on both sides of the contract aware of their rights and obligations.</p><p> </p><p>1 Acceptance</p><p> </p><p>1.1 By registering as a member of Honest Day\'s Work you accept these terms and conditions and will adhere to them.</p><p>1.2 Occasionally Honest Day\'s Work will amend these terms and conditions. We will advise you by email or by site notification. We will generally give you a month to review these changes. Amendments will become effective immediately once posted on the Honest Day\'s Work website. It is your responsibility to ensure you are familiar with the latest terms and conditions. Your continued use of our services will represent your agreement to the amended terms and conditions.</p><p> </p><p>2 Membership</p><p> </p><p>2.1 Becoming a Member: Becoming a member is free. You may only register as a member if you are resident in New Zealand or Australia (unless specifically authorised by us in writing) and can form a legally binding contract that is enforceable against you. You must be at least 18 years old. By registering as a member, you warrant that you can form a legally binding contract.</p><p>Honest Day\'s Work may, at its sole discretion, refuse the services to anyone at any time.</p><p> </p><p>2.2 Accurate Information: You warrant that you have provided complete, accurate and current personal information when registering as a member. You must maintain and update your personal information held by Honest Day\'s Work to ensure it is kept current at all times. Honest Day\'s Work may phone or mail you to verify these details. You must not register as a member under multiple identities or personas (whether false or not). However, at Honest Day\'s Work\'s discretion, you may create a business membership in addition to your personal membership.</p><p> </p><p>2.3 Termination of membership: Honest Day\'s Work reserves the right to decline to register or to terminate your membership without entering into further discussions with you. Without limiting the foregoing, Honest Day\'s Work may terminate your membership if a serious complaint or multiple complaints are received about you from other members, if you breach these terms and conditions, if you impersonate another member, or if we, at our sole discretion, deem your behaviour to be unacceptable. Members who have registered under multiple aliases will have all of their aliases disabled. When limiting your activities on the Website Honest Day\'s Work may consider offsite conduct such as prior criminal convictions, insolvency, or any other conduct that puts our community or systems at risk. In the event of termination, you also agree that you will not open or attempt to open any new Honest Day\'s Work memberships. You may at any time close your Honest Day\'s Work membership by giving us three days\' notice in writing. If you close your membership, or if it is terminated by Honest Day\'s Work, your ability to use the Honest Day\'s Work website will end.</p><p> </p><p>2.4 Security of your login information: You are responsible for keeping your login information, including your email address and password, secret and secure. Without limiting the foregoing, you agree:</p><p> </p><p>not to permit any other person to use your user name or membership; and</p><p> </p><p>not to disclose, or provide to any other person, your password, email address, date of birth or any other information in connection with your membership that may allow them to gain access to your membership.</p><p>You agree to immediately inform Honest Day\'s Work of any unauthorised use of your password or username, including that of your general user 