k.</p><p> </p><p>You must not use the Services or the Website to promote services for sale outside the Services.</p><p> </p><p>You are responsible for any actions taken through your membership. Honest Day\'s Work memberships are not transferable and therefore cannot be sold, leased, lent or traded without specific written authorisation from Honest Day\'s Work.</p><p> </p><p>3.2 Your obligations as a Contractor/Seller</p><p> </p><p>Contractors/Sellers must be located in New Zealand or Australia. Contractors/Sellers outside of these countries are not permitted to submit tenders on Honest Day\'s Work, unless specifically authorised in writing by Honest Day\'s Work.</p><p> </p><p>You will only submit tender proposals that are accurate, current, complete, and include all relevant information about the terms of sale and payment terms. It is your responsibility to ensure that your Tender Submissions are fully compliant with the terms and conditions contained in a relevant Tender Bid and any amendments thereto from the Procuring Party. Honest Day\'s Work will not be liable in any way for your failure for any reason to comply with such terms and conditions.</p><p> </p><p>You will only submit tenders for contracts that you are legally entitled, qualified and competent to complete.</p><p> </p><p>It is your responsibility to ensure that all data uploaded to the Honest Day\'s Work website is in a standardised electronic form compatible with both Honest Day\'s Work and the buyers’ requirements. To clarify the appropriate data formats you should contact either Honest Day\'s Work or the buyer via the question and answer forum for the tender. Failure to upload data in the correct format may render your tender null and void.</p><p> </p><p>All tender submissions must comply with New Zealand law. You must not submit anything that is illegal, offensive (including anything of a defamatory, pornographic, or racially or ethnically objectionable nature), or unsafe, or any proposal of which 