of your general user accounts and to ensure that you do not allow third parties to use your account.</p><p> </p><p>2.5 Emails and newsletters: Honest Day\'s Work will send you emails relating to your membership, transactions and other activities on the Website, and for promoting and marketing other Honest Day\'s Work products and Services to you. Honest Day\'s Work may also send regular electronic newsletters to members. Newsletters will contain clear and obvious instructions for how you can unsubscribe from the mailing list.</p><p> </p><p>3 General</p><p> </p><p>3.1 General</p><p> </p><p>All tenders, tender submissions or communications made through Honest Day\'s Work shall be made in good faith.</p><p> </p><p>You must not damage, interfere with or harm the Website or Services, or any network, or system underlying or connected to them, or attempt to do so.</p><p> </p><p>You may not use a robot, spider, scraper or other unauthorised automated means to access the Website or information featured on it for any purpose.</p><p> </p><p>You shall not list your email address, phone number or any other contact detail within the description of the tender, listing comments and/or questions, in your member profile, or in the Honest Day\'s Work message boards, except where expressly required by Honest Day\'s Work in the contact fields.</p><p> </p><p>You must list tenders in New Zealand dollars and include GST in all tender submissions. GST shall be clearly marked by the tenderers on any submitted tender schedules or pricing detail. All tax obligations are the responsibility of the seller and/or the buyer (as the parties determine).</p><p> </p><p>You must not complete a transaction outside of the Honest Day\'s Work process or otherwise seek to avoid Honest Day\'s Work\'s fees. Attempts by you to avoid fees, including through multiple memberships, premature tender withdrawal, or otherwise, may result in Honest Day\'s Work suspending or terminating your membership at the discretion of Honest Day\'s Work.</p><p> </p><p>You must not use the Services or the Website to promote services for sale outside the Services.</p><p> </p><p>You are responsible for any actions taken through your membership. Honest Day\'s Work memberships are not transferable and therefore cannot be sold, leased, lent or traded without specific written authorisation from Honest Day\'s Work.</p><p> </p><p>3.2 Your obligations as a Contractor/Seller</p><p> </p><p>Contractors/Sellers must be located in New Zealand or Australia. Contractors/Sellers outside of these countries are not permitted to submit tenders on Honest Day\'s Work, unless specifically authorised in writing by Honest Day\'s Work.</p><p> </p><p>You will only submit tender proposals that are accurate, current, complete, and include all relevant information about the terms of sale and payment terms. It is your responsibility to ensure that your Tender Submissions are fully compliant with the terms and conditions contained in a relevant Tender Bid and any amendments thereto from the Procuring Party. Honest Day\'s Work will not be liable in any way for your failure for any reason to comply with such terms and conditions.</p><p> </p><p>You will only submit tenders for contracts that you are legally entitled, qualified and competent to complete.</p><p> </p><p>It is your responsibility to ensure that all data uploaded to the Honest Day\'s Work website is in a standardised electronic form compatible with both Honest Day\'s Work and the buyers’ requirements. To clarify the appropriate data formats you should contact either Honest Day\'s Work or the buyer via the question and answer forum for the tender. Failure to upload data in the correct format may render your tender null and void.</p><p> </p><p>All tender submissions must comply with New Zealand law. You must not submit anything that is illegal, offensive (including anything of a defamatory, pornographic, or racially or ethnically objectionable nature), or unsafe, or any proposal of which the transaction is prohibited by, or violates any, law. You are responsible for ensuring that any tender submitted by you does not breach this clause 4.2(f). You agree that Honest Day\'s Work may disclose your personal information, including your name and contact details, to the relevant authorities, parties and/or the applicable intellectual property right holders (or their representatives) if we consider that you are in breach of this clause at any time.</p><p> </p><p>You must ensure you hold the copyright or are otherwise licensed to use any images you add to your tender submissions.</p><p> </p><p>Your tender submission may only contain a URL for a website that contains further information on the submission you have listed. This website must not offer any services for sale, or contain contact details. You must not use Honest Day\'s Work tender listings to promote a business or website.</p><p> </p><p>You must not manipulate tenders through shill-bidding or assuming multiple roles in a single transaction.</p><p> </p><p>Your submitted tender and submitted price is not retractable once the tender has closed. You must only submit a tender if you intend to commit to the contract should you be selected as the winning tenderer.</p><p>If you are notified that your tender submission has been successful, you must complete the transaction in the manner specified. By making a tender submission you warrant and represent that you have the legal right to enter into and complete the transaction.</p><p> </p><p>You agree to your email address and name being provided to the buyer when the tender closes.</p><p> </p><p>It is the buyer’s responsibility to notify winning tenderers.</p><p> </p><p>If you are selected as the winning tenderer You must promptly begin the contract for the buyer or as may be otherwise described in the contract agreement.</p><p> </p><p>You agree to your username and the amount of your winning tender being publicly shown on the Honest Day\'s Work Website.</p><p> </p><p>If you are selected as the winning tenderer but do not complete the contract, you will receive a warning from Honest Day\'s Work if the seller complains about you. After 3 such complaints, Honest Day\'s Work may suspend or terminate your membership.</p><p> </p><p>3.3 Your obligations as a Purchaser/Client</p><p> </p><p>You must be located in New Zealand or Australia to list tenders on Honest Day\'s Work. People outside of these countries are not permitted to create tenders on Honest Day\'s Work.</p><p> </p><p>Tenders are not pre-screened for content. Honest Day\'s Work reserves the right to remove any tender that it deems unsuitable or in breach of the terms and conditions.</p><p> </p><p>When you create a tender on Honest Day\'s Work, you should do so with the intention of awarding this contract through the site. Therefore you should not advertise your proposal through another forum. If you remove a tender you may incur a non-refundable withdrawal fee, regardless of the reason.</p><p> </p><p>You agree to your email address being provided to the tenderers when your tender closes.</p><p> </p><p>You must make full and prompt payment for any service/contract you buy, or as may be otherwise described in the contract agreement.</p><p> </p><p>If you do not pay for the contract as required by the contract documents or the contract agreement, you will receive a warning from Honest Day\'s Work if the seller complains about you. After 3 such complaints, Honest Day\'s Work may suspend or terminate your membership.</p><p> </p><p>3.4 Feedback</p><p> </p><p>Feedback is provided for the purpose of facilitating trading between members on the Honest Day\'s Work Website. Feedback you provide on other members must not contain offensive, defamatory, retaliatory or inappropriate language or content. Honest Day\'s Work may remove any feedback that we consider to be offensive, defamatory, retaliatory or inappropriate.</p><p> </p><p>You may only give member feedback that relates to a specific contract or tender. You must not post feedback on a contract or tender that does not relate to that specific contract or tender.</p><p> </p><p>You must not post feedback about yourself or include any contact details or personal information in your feedback.</p><p> </p><p>4 Fair and Honest Representation</p><p> </p><p>4.1 The Services: Honest Day\'s Work provides a venue to introduce members who want to negotiate contracts. Honest Day\'s Work does not take any part in the purchase or sale of services, products or contracts other than by providing our Website as a venue for members. If a contract is accepted by a purchaser, a contract will be formed between the purchaser and the seller directly. We do not act as agent for either party and do not participate in any purchase, sale or transaction between you and other members.</p><p> </p><p>4.2 At your own risk: Transactions and all other contact between you and other members are conducted entirely at your own risk. You agree that Honest Day\'s Work takes no responsibility or liability for any misconduct of any of its members including,  members that have registered under false pretences or who attempt to defraud you. Honest Day\'s Work gives no undertakings, representations, or warranties in relation to contracts tendered, listed or awarded on the Website including:</p><ul><li>the content, safety, description, worthiness, quality, or legality of the contracts or services that are procured on the Website;</li>\n<li>the accuracy or truth of tender details;</li>\n<li>that any tender submitted or awarded will meet your requirements or expectations; or</li>\n<li>about the ability of members to complete a transaction.</li>\n</ul><p> </p><p>4.3 Disclaimer: You understand and agree that:</p><p> </p><p>Your use of the Services is at your sole risk. The Website and Services are provided on an \"as is\" and \"as available\" basis. To the maximum extent permitted by law.</p><p> </p><p>Honest Day\'s Work disclaims and excludes liability for any guarantees that a contract will be carried out with reasonable care and skill, fitness for a particular purpose, time of completion or price for the contract;</p><p> </p><p>Honest Day\'s Work does not warrant that i) the Services provided will be uninterrupted, timely, secure, or error free, or ii) that any information (including feedback) provided on the Website is error-free or reliable;</p><p> </p><p>No advice or information that is obtained by you from Honest Day\'s Work or anyone else shall create any warranty by Honest Day\'s Work that is not expressly stated in the terms and conditions; and</p><p> </p><p>Responsibility for the content of advertisements appearing on this Website (including hyperlinks to advertisers\' own websites) rests solely with the advertisers. The placement of such advertisements on the Website does not constitute Honest Day\'s Work\'s recommendation or endorsement of the advertised product or service. Each advertiser is solely responsible for any representation made in connection with its advertisement.</p><p> </p><p>While Honest Day\'s Work may facilitate payment for some items by credit card, Honest Day\'s Work is in no way involved in the Contract transaction itself, and responsibility for any refund rests with the seller.</p><p> </p><p>While Honest Day\'s Work has systems in place to reduce the risk of credit card fraud, Honest Day\'s Work is not responsible for protecting members from credit card fraud. Honest Day\'s Work\'s fraud protection systems may from time to time block legitimate credit card payments. In these cases payment will need to be made by other means.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>4.4 Liability: To the maximum extent permitted by law, any and all liability and responsibility of Honest Day\'s Work to you or any other person under or in connection with these terms and conditions, or in connection with the services, this Website, another Member\'s acts or omissions, or your use of or inability to use, the services or this Website, is excluded regardless of whether such liability arises in contract, tort (including negligence), equity, breach of statutory duty or otherwise. Honest Day\'s Work\'s liability and responsibility is excluded in respect of any and all loss or damage, whether direct or indirect, including, without limitation, loss of profits, loss of data, loss of business or anticipated savings, general and special damages, and consequential and incidental loss.</p><p> </p><p>4.5 Indemnity: You agree to release, indemnify and keep indemnified us from and against all actions, claims, costs (including legal costs and expenses), losses, proceedings, damages, liabilities, or demands suffered or incurred by us to any person arising out of or in connection with your failure to comply with these terms and conditions, your failure to complete a transaction, your use of Honest Day\'s Work\'s message boards, your contract or attempted sale of services prohibited under clause 4.2(f).</p><p> </p><p>4.6 Breach: Without limiting any other rights and remedies available to Honest Day\'s Work, Honest Day\'s Work may limit your activities on the Website, remove your tenders, listings or other content, warn other members of your actions, issue a warning to you, suspend or terminate your membership, or refuse to provide our Services to you if you breach these terms and conditions, or where Honest Day\'s Work considers it appropriate.</p><p> </p><p>5 Fees</p><p> </p><p>The Honest Day\'s Work\'s current fees, which are charged for the use of the Website, are listed on our fees page in the FAQ section. Fees may be changed at any time and will be listed in the FAQ section. All fees are GST inclusive and listed in New Zealand dollars. You should review the fees prior to using our service. The non-payment of fees will result in Tenders not being listed (for Purchasers) or Tender Submissions not being submitted (for Sellers).</p><p> </p><p>6 General</p><p> </p>