(227, 16, 24, 1, 2, 2, 'Page', '2018-01-26 14:11:38', '2017-11-10 13:32:44', 'resources-for-preparing-tenders', 'Resources for Preparing Tenders', NULL, '<p>This material is provided to give guidance on common tendering practices in New Zealand. If you are preparing a tender, read the information below. If you are submitting a tender, click <a title=\"Resources for Submitting Tenders\" href=\"[sitetree_link,id=17]\">here</a>.</p><p> </p><p>When preparing tender documentation it is important to understand the level of risk you are comfortable with. For example if you are setting up a tender for the construction of a fence, and you believe the cost is around $1,000, you may be comfortable with specifying all your requirements through photos, a sketch and a description of the work. If a dispute arose around some aspect of the work then this could be dealt with by negotiation or in the Small Claims Tribunal and the cost at stake may be manageable.</p><p> </p><p>If the tender being set up was for the construction of a house then the level of risk would be significantly higher and it would be necessary to have drawings and tender documentation prepared to ensure both parties understood what was required, when payments would be made, what would happen if the work was delayed etc. The investment in time/cost to prepare the documents would be worthwhile considering the risk being managed.</p><p> </p><p>Below are templates and guidance on common aspects of tendering. If you are not sure if you need these documents or not it is always best to consult a professional.</p><p> </p><h2>Drawings/Sketches</h2><p>A simple job such as a fence may just require a sketch showing the location, length, height, foundations etc. Larger jobs will often require pages of detailed drawings showing precise measurements and critical features of the work.</p><p> </p><h2>Conditions of Tendering</h2><p>Conditions of Tendering describe the rules of the tendering and tender assessment process. This ensures that both Tenderers and the Client understand what information needs to be provided with the Tender and the process the Client will go through to assess and award the contract.</p><p> </p><h2>Standard Conditions</h2><p>Standard Conditions is a document which sets out the rules and method of managing a contract. Common standards used in New Zealand are:</p><p>· <a title=\"NZS 3910:2013\" href=\"https://shop.standards.govt.nz/catalog/3910%3A2013%28NZS%29/view\">NZS 3910:2013</a> - Construction (link is to the scope only)</p><p>· <a title=\"NZS 3916:2013\" href=\"https://shop.standards.govt.nz/catalog/3916%3A2013%28NZS%29/view?client=html5\">NZS 3916:2013</a> - Design and Construct (link is to the scope only)</p><p>· <a title=\"NZS 3917:2013\" href=\"https://shop.standards.govt.nz/catalog/3917%3A2013%28NZS%29/view\">NZS 3917:2013</a> - Fixed Term (link is to the scope only)</p><p>Other standards are also available.</p><p> </p><h2>Special Conditions</h2><p>Special conditions modify the standard conditions so that the conditions better suit the needs/complexities of your own project. The special conditions are drafted up on a case by case basis.</p><p> </p><h2>Estimate</h2><p>For some jobs, particularly large and complex work, it is helpful to provide an estimate for the Tenderers. Normally this is prepared by an Engineer or someone who has a good understanding of the work. This will help the Tenderers quickly gauge the scope of the work and your expectations around the cost.</p><p> </p><h2>Schedule of Prices</h2><p>A schedule of prices is a breakdown of the price structure line by line. It provides the Tenderers with a format for breaking down their price which makes it easy to compare particular items between Tenders submitted. Once the job is awarded the schedule then provides a means of recording and claiming costs as the work is progressively completed. Essential for complex jobs.</p><p> </p><h2>Terms/Basis of Payment</h2><p>Terms of Payment (or Basis of Payment), describes how and when payments will be made. This is important for work which may span several months, is high risk or has more than one or two elements. Usually the Terms of Payment will refer directly to the schedule of prices and describe how each line item will be paid.</p><p> </p><h2>Specification</h2><p>A specification is a written document which describes the requirements of the work. This could be a short document for simple work or a larger document for more complex work. Normally it would contain sections which align with the schedule of prices and the drawings. Often the specification will refer to well known standards, ensuring the work is completed to best practice. Essential for complex work.</p><p> </p><h2>Extra Reading</h2><p>The New Zealand government have rules for government agency procurement and tendering. While these may be a lot to read through and more onerous than what is required for your job, they do contain some good principals that will help you understand the process. Other useful references are also provided:</p><p><a title=\"The Five Principals of Government Procurement\" href=\"http://www.procurement.govt.nz/procurement/pdf-library/agencies/rules-of-sourcing/five-principles-of-government-procurement.PDF\" target=\"_blank\">The Five Principles of Government Procurement</a></p><p><a title=\"Government Rules of Sourcing\" href=\"http://www.procurement.govt.nz/procurement/pdf-library/agencies/rules-of-sourcing/procurement-government-rules-of-sourcing-v3.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Government Rules of Sourcing</a></p><p><a href=\"http://www.clendons.co.nz/resources/background-papers/law-tendering/\">Law of Tendering</a></p><p><a title=\"Tenders and Quotes\" href=\"https://www.building.govt.nz/projects-and-consents/planning-a-successful-build/scope-and-design/choosing-the-right-people-for-your-type-of-building-work/tenders-and-quotes/\">Tenders and Quotes</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>', NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 15, 0, 0, NULL, 'Inherit', 'Inherit', 2),
(228, 17, 10, 1, 2, 2, 'Page', '2018-01-26 14:11:55', '2017-11-10 14:08:39', 'resources-for-submitting-tenders', 'Resources for Submitting Tenders', NULL, '<p>This material is provided to give guidance on common tendering practices in New Zealand. If you are preparing a tender, read the information below. If you are preparing a tender, click here.</p><p> </p><p>The key to submitting a competitive tender is to understand  the clients needs. The client may not select the lowest price if it is evident that that tenderer did not understand critical elements of the job. Use the forum in the tender to ask the client questions about the job, particularly if you can see risks or it is evident the client is unsure about the job.</p><p> </p><p>Each tender will require different supporting information, check well in advance of the tender close date what is required to be submitted and ensure you have enough time to prepare the documentation. If the client hasn\'t provided enough time to prepare the necessary documentation, ask them why - it may be that they don\'t understand how much time you need to prepare the submission and they may choose to extend the submission date.</p><p> </p><p>Some external websites for further reading:</p><p><a href=\"http://www.procurement.govt.nz/procurement/for-suppliers/resources-for-responding-to-government-tenders/hints-for-tendering\">Hints for Tendering</a></p><p><a title=\"Tendering Handbook\" href=\"http://industryadvocate.sa.gov.au/upload/industry-advocate/resources-downloads/tender-ready-handbook.pdf?t=1505174400023\">Tendering Handbook</a> (South Australia)</p><p><a title=\"How to Lose Tenders\" href=\"http://www.plana.co.nz/how-lose-tenders\">How to Lose Tenders</a></p><p> </p>', NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 16, 0, 0, NULL, 'Inherit', 'Inherit', 2),
(229, 13, 14, 1, 2, 2, 'Page', '2018-01-26 14:15:33', '2017-10-27 12:43:22', 'terms-and-conditions', 'Terms and Conditions', NULL, '<p>Terms and conditions, last updated 15 December 2017</p><p> </p><p>Honest Day\'s Work objective is to connect people who need work completed with those who need work to complete. The terms and conditions below help to keep parties on both sides of the contract aware of their rights and obligations.</p><p> </p><h2>1 Acceptance</h2><p> </p><p>1.1 By registering as a member of Honest Day\'s Work you accept these terms and conditions and will adhere to them.</p><p>1.2 Occasionally Honest Day\'s Work will amend these terms and conditions. We will advise you by email or by site notification. We will generally give you a month to review these changes. Amendments will become effective immediately once posted on the Honest Day\'s Work website. It is your responsibility to ensure you are familiar with the latest terms and conditions. Your continued use of our services will represent your agreement to the amended terms and conditions.</p><p> </p><h2>2 Membership</h2><p> </p><p>2.1 Becoming a Member: Becoming a member is free. You may only register as a member if you are resident in New Zealand or Australia (unless specifically authorised by us in writing) and can form a legally binding contract that is enforceable against you. You must be at least 18 years old. By registering as a member, you warrant that you can form a legally binding contract.</p><p>Honest Day\'s Work may, at its sole discretion, refuse the services to anyone at any time.</p><p> </p><p>2.2 Accurate Information: You warrant that you have provided complete, accurate and current personal information when registering as a member. You must maintain and update your personal information held by Honest Day\'s Work to ensure it is kept current at all times. Honest Day\'s Work may phone or mail you to verify these details. You must not register as a member under multiple identities or personas (whether false or not). However, at Honest Day\'s Work\'s discretion, you may create a business membership in addition to your personal membership.</p><p> </p><p>2.3 Termination of membership: Honest Day\'s Work reserves the right to decline to register or to terminate your membership without entering into further discussions with you. Without limiting the foregoing, Honest Day\'s Work may terminate your membership if a serious complaint or multiple complaints are received about you from other members, if you breach these terms and conditions, if you impersonate another member, or if we, at our sole discretion, deem your behaviour to be unacceptable. Members who have registered under multiple aliases will have all of their aliases disabled. When limiting your activities on the Website Honest Day\'s Work may consider offsite conduct such as prior criminal convictions, insolvency, or any other conduct that puts our community or systems at risk. In the event of termination, you also agree that you will not open or attempt to open any new Honest Day\'s Work memberships. You may at any time close your Honest Day\'s Work membership by giving us three days\' notice in writing. If you close your membership, or if it is terminated by Honest Day\'s Work, your ability to use the Honest Day\'s Work website will end.</p><p> </p><p>2.4 Security of your login information: You are responsible for keeping your login information, including your email address and password, secret and secure. Without limiting the foregoing, you agree:</p><p> </p><p>not to permit any other person to use your user name or membership; and</p><p> </p><p>not to disclose, or provide to any other person, your password, email address, date of birth or any other information in connection with your membership that may allow them to gain access to your membership.</p><p>You agree to immediately inform Honest Day\'s Work of any unauthorised use of your password or username, including that of your general user accounts and to ensure that you do not allow third parties to use your account.</p><p> </p><p>2.5 Emails and newsletters: Honest Day\'s Work will send you emails relating to your membership, transactions and other activities on the Website, and for promoting and marketing other Honest Day\'s Work products and Services to you. Honest Day\'s Work may also send regular electronic newsletters to members. Newsletters will contain clear and obvious instructions for how you can unsubscribe from the mailing list.</p><p> </p><h2>3 General</h2><p> </p><p>3.1 General</p><p> </p><p>All tenders, tender submissions or communications made through Honest Day\'s Work shall be made in good faith.</p><p> </p><p>You must not damage, interfere with or harm the Website or Services, or any network, or system underlying or connected to them, or attempt to do so.</p><p> </p><p>You may not use a robot, spider, scraper or other unauthorised automated means to access the Website or information featured on it for any purpose.</p><p> </p><p>You shall not list your email address, phone number or any other contact detail within the description of the tender, listing comments and/or questions, in your member profile, or in the Honest Day\'s Work message boards, except where expressly required by Honest Day\'s Work in the contact fields.</p><p> </p><p>You must list tenders in New Zealand dollars and include GST in all tender submissions. GST shall be clearly marked by the tenderers on any submitted tender schedules or pricing detail. All tax obligations are the responsibility of the seller and/or the buyer (as the parties determine).</p><p> </p><p>You must not complete a transaction outside of the Honest Day\'s Work process or otherwise seek to avoid Honest Day\'s Work\'s fees. Attempts by you to avoid fees, including through multiple memberships, premature tender withdrawal, or otherwise, may result in Honest Day\'s Work suspending or terminating your membership at the discretion of Honest Day\'s Work.</p><p> </p><p>You must not use the Services or the Website to promote services for sale outside the Services.</p><p> </p><p>You are responsible for any actions taken through your membership. Honest Day\'s Work memberships are not transferable and therefore cannot be sold, leased, lent or traded without specific written authorisation from Honest Day\'s Work.</p><p> </p><p>3.2 Your obligations as a Contractor/Seller</p><p> </p><p>Contractors/Sellers must be located in New Zealand or Australia. Contractors/Sellers outside of these countries are not permitted to submit tenders on Honest Day\'s Work, unless specifically authorised in writing by Honest Day\'s Work.</p><p> </p><p>You will only submit tender proposals that are accurate, current, complete, and include all relevant information about the terms of sale and payment terms. It is your responsibility to ensure that your Tender Submissions are fully compliant with the terms and conditions contained in a relevant Tender Bid and any amendments thereto from the Procuring Party. Honest Day\'s Work will not be liable in any way for your failure for any reason to comply with such terms and conditions.</p><p> </p><p>You will only submit tenders for contracts that you are legally entitled, qualified and competent to complete.</p><p> </p><p>It is your responsibility to ensure that all data uploaded to the Honest Day\'s Work website is in a standardised electronic form compatible with both Honest Day\'s Work and the buyers’ requirements. To clarify the appropriate data formats you should contact either Honest Day\'s Work or the buyer via the question and answer forum for the tender. Failure to upload data in the correct format may render your tender null and void.</p><p> </p><p>All tender submissions must comply with New Zealand law. You must not submit anything that is illegal, offensive (including anything of a defamatory, pornographic, or racially or ethnically objectionable nature), or unsafe, or any proposal of which the transaction is prohibited by, or violates any, law. You are responsible for ensuring that any tender submitted by you does not breach this clause 4.2(f). You agree that Honest Day\'s Work may disclose your personal information, including your name and contact details, to the relevant authorities, parties and/or the applicable intellectual property right holders (or their representatives) if we consider that you are in breach of this clause at any time.</p><p> </p><p>You must ensure you hold the copyright or are otherwise licensed to use any images you add to your tender submissions.</p><p> </p><p>Your tender submission may only contain a URL for a website that contains further information on the submission you have listed. This website must not offer any services for sale, or contain contact details. You must not use Honest Day\'s Work tender listings to promote a business or website.</p><p> </p><p>You must not manipulate tenders through shill-bidding or assuming multiple roles in a single transaction.</p><p> </p><p>Your submitted tender and submitted price is not retractable once the tender has closed. You must only submit a tender if you intend to commit to the contract should you be selected as the winning tenderer.</p><p>If you are notified that your tender submission has been successful, you must complete the transaction in the manner specified. By making a tender submission you warrant and represent that you have the legal right to enter into and complete the transaction.</p><p> </p><p>You agree to your email address and name being provided to the buyer when the tender closes.</p><p> </p><p>It is the buyer’s responsibility to notify winning tenderers.</p><p> </p><p>If you are selected as the winning tenderer You must promptly begin the contract for the buyer or as may be otherwise described in the contract agreement.</p><p> </p><p>You agree to your username and the amount of your winning tender being publicly shown on the Honest Day\'s Work Website.</p><p> </p><p>If you are selected as the winning tenderer but do not complete the contract, you will receive a warning from Honest Day\'s Work if the seller complains about you. After 3 such complaints, Honest Day\'s Work may suspend or terminate your membership.</p><p> </p><p>3.3 Your obligations as a Purchaser/Client</p><p> </p><p>You must be located in New Zealand or Australia to list tenders on Honest Day\'s Work. People outside of these countries are not permitted to create tenders on Honest Day\'s Work.</p><p> </p><p>Tenders are not pre-screened for content. Honest Day\'s Work reserves the right to remove any tender that it deems unsuitable or in breach of the terms and conditions.</p><p> </p><p>When you create a tender on Honest Day\'s Work, you should do so with the intention of awarding this contract through the site. Therefore you should not advertise your proposal through another forum. If you remove a tender you may incur a non-refundable withdrawal fee, regardless of the reason.</p><p> </p><p>You agree to your email address being provided to the tenderers when your tender closes.</p><p> </p><p>You must make full and prompt payment for any service/contract you buy, or as may be otherwise described in the contract agreement.</p><p> </p><p>If you do not pay for the contract as required by the contract documents or the contract agreement, you will receive a warning from Honest Day\'s Work if the seller complains about you. After 3 such complaints, Honest Day\'s Work may suspend or terminate your membership.</p><p> </p><p>3.4 Feedback</p><p> </p><p>Feedback is provided for the purpose of facilitating trading between members on the Honest Day\'s Work Website. Feedback you provide on other members must not contain offensive, defamatory, retaliatory or inappropriate language or content. Honest Day\'s Work may remove any feedback that we consider to be offensive, defamatory, retaliatory or inappropriate.</p><p> </p><p>You may only give member feedback that relates to a specific contract or tender. You must not post feedback on a contract or tender that does not relate to that specific contract or tender.</p><p> </p><p>You must not post feedback about yourself or include any contact details or personal information in your feedback.</p><p> </p><h2>4 Fair and Honest Representation</h2><p> </p><p>4.1 The Services: Honest Day\'s Work provides a venue to introduce members who want to negotiate contracts. Honest Day\'s Work does not take any part in the purchase or sale of services, products or contracts other than by providing our Website as a venue for members. If a contract is accepted by a purchaser, a contract will be formed between the purchaser and the seller directly. We do not act as agent for either party and do not participate in any purchase, sale or transaction between you and other members.</p><p> </p><p>4.2 At your own risk: Transactions and all other contact between you and other members are conducted entirely at your own risk. You agree that Honest Day\'s Work takes no responsibility or liability for any misconduct of any of its members including,  members that have registered under false pretences or who attempt to defraud you. Honest Day\'s Work gives no undertakings, representations, or warranties in relation to contracts tendered, listed or awarded on the Website including:</p><ul><li>the content, safety, description, worthiness, quality, or legality of the contracts or services that are procured on the Website;</li>\n<li>the accuracy or truth of tender details;</li>\n<li>that any tender submitted or awarded will meet your requirements or expectations; or</li>\n<li>about the ability of members to complete a transaction.</li>\n</ul><p> </p><p>4.3 Disclaimer: You understand and agree that:</p><p> </p><p>Your use of the Services is at your sole risk. The Website and Services are provided on an \"as is\" and \"as available\" basis. To the maximum extent permitted by law.</p><p> </p><p>Honest Day\'s Work disclaims and excludes liability for any guarantees that a contract will be carried out with reasonable care and skill, fitness for a particular purpose, time of completion or price for the contract;</p><p> </p><p>Honest Day\'s Work does not warrant that i) the Services provided will be uninterrupted, timely, secure, or error free, or ii) that any information (including feedback) provided on the Website is error-free or reliable;</p><p> </p><p>No advice or information that is obtained by you from Honest Day\'s Work or anyone else shall create any warranty by Honest Day\'s Work that is not expressly stated in the terms and conditions; and</p><p> </p><p>Responsibility for the content of advertisements appearing on this Website (including hyperlinks to advertisers\' own websites) rests solely with the advertisers. The placement of such advertisements on the Website does not constitute Honest Day\'s Work\'s recommendation or endorsement of the advertised product or service. Each advertiser is solely responsible for any representation made in connection with its advertisement.</p><p> </p><p>While Honest Day\'s Work may facilitate payment for some items by credit card, Honest Day\'s Work is in no way involved in the Contract transaction itself, and responsibility for any refund rests with the seller.</p><p> </p><p>While Honest Day\'s Work has systems in place to reduce the risk of credit card fraud, Honest Day\'s Work is not responsible for protecting members from credit card fraud. Honest Day\'s Work\'s fraud protection systems may from time to time block legitimate credit card payments. In these cases payment will need to be made by other means.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>4.4 Liability: To the maximum extent permitted by law, any and all liability and responsibility of Honest Day\'s Work to you or any other person under or in connection with these terms and conditions, or in connection with the services, this Website, another Member\'s acts or omissions, or your use of or inability to use, the services or this Website, is excluded regardless of whether such liability arises in contract, tort (including negligence), equity, breach of statutory duty or otherwise. Honest Day\'s Work\'s liability and responsibility is excluded in respect of any and all loss or damage, whether direct or indirect, including, without limitation, loss of profits, loss of data, loss of business or anticipated savings, general and special damages, and consequential and incidental loss.</p><p> </p><p>4.5 Indemnity: You agree to release, indemnify and keep indemnified us from and against all actions, claims, costs (including legal costs and expenses), losses, proceedings, damages, liabilities, or demands suffered or incurred by us to any person arising out of or in connection with your failure to comply with these terms and conditions, your failure to complete a transaction, your use of Honest Day\'s Work\'s message boards, your contract or attempted sale of services prohibited under clause 4.2(f).</p><p> </p><p>4.6 Breach: Without limiting any other rights and remedies available to Honest Day\'s Work, Honest Day\'s Work may limit your activities on the Website, remove your tenders, listings or other content, warn other members of your actions, issue a warning to you, suspend or terminate your membership, or refuse to provide our Services to you if you breach these terms and conditions, or where Honest Day\'s Work considers it appropriate.</p><p> </p><h2>5 Fees</h2><p> </p><p>The Honest Day\'s Work\'s current fees, which are charged for the use of the Website, are listed on our fees page in the FAQ section. Fees may be changed at any time and will be listed in the FAQ section. All fees are GST inclusive and listed in New Zealand dollars. You should review the fees prior to using our service. The non-payment of fees will result in Tenders not being listed (for Purchasers) or Tender Submissions not being submitted (for Sellers).</p><p> </p><h2>6 General</h2><p> </p><p>6.1 Website Availability: Honest Day\'s Work will use its reasonable endeavours to ensure the availability of the Website and Services, subject to any downtime required for maintenance. However, Honest Day\'s Work takes no responsibility for any system unavailability, or for any loss that is incurred as a result of Website or Services being unavailable. Further, Honest Day\'s Work assumes no responsibility for the corruption of any data or information held by Honest Day\'s Work and holds no liability for any lack of performance due to causes outside the control of Honest Day’s Work.</p><p> </p><p>6.2 Disputes: As Honest Day\'s Work is not a party to any sale or transaction between you and another member, you agree not to involve, or attempt to involve, Honest Day\'s Work in any dispute or in the resolution of disputes that arise between you and another member as a result of the Services provided. If you wish to take Proceedings against another member, you can contact Honest Day\'s Work for a statutory declaration form, which must be completed before we will consider releasing anyone else\'s information to you. You may only request contact details for the sole purpose of making a claim.</p><p> </p><p>6.3 Intellectual Property Rights: Honest Day\'s Work owns all proprietary and intellectual property rights in the Website (including text, graphics, logos, icons and sound recordings) and the software and other material underlying and forming part of the Services and the Website.</p><p> </p><p>6.4 Entire agreement: These terms and conditions supersede all previous conditions, understandings, commitments, agreements and representations whatsoever whether oral or written, and constitutes the entire agreement, between the parties, relating to the subject matter of these terms and conditions.</p><p> </p><h2>7 Terminology</h2><p>\'Tender\' includes both \'open tenders\' and \'closed tenders\' and refers to a listing on the website which you purchase, negotiate, offer, buy, sell or 