(313, 'Tender', '2018-06-29 21:00:01', '2018-06-15 12:20:06', 'Fence replacement', 'This property needs all 4 fences scrapped and replaced with solid corrugated iron fencing around all perimeters. \r\nThe house is owned by my mother and I own the back property. \r\nOriginally the fences in the front were never installed correctly, resulting in them falling over. \r\nThe contractor will have to rip out the fences, dispose of all unusable materials (we are happy to pay for a skip bin for the rubbish), concrete in some new posts at a reasonable depth, and clad with corrugated iron.\r\n\r\n1. The street facing fence is approx. 17-18m long and only needs to be a metre high.\r\n2. the driveway fence is 30m long and only required to be the same height of 1 metre.\r\nThe driveway on the other side leads to my house, so the neighbours will be easy to work with, lol.\r\nThese fences had our mailboxes attached to them, they blew over in the storm, so if these could be fixed into place as well. \r\n3. the south side fence needs to be at least 180cm high, with a horse wire placed on the side facing the neighbours house. They are amenable to having this fence fixed.\r\n4. The fence inbetween these two properties needs to be mended. If the trees are in the way, we are happy for them to be cut right back or even disposed of (except the lemon tree).\r\nThe ground condition is typical of Kaiti - one foot down you will hit clay, but we need the fence posts to be dug deeper than this. There is usually a lot of surface water, especially after a big rain in winter. \r\n\r\nWe would like work to start on this asap, as the tenants in the property have small children and we don\'t want any more fences falling down. ', 258, '12', 'Lorraine Street', 'Gisborne', 'Gisborne', '4010', 'New Zealand', -38.6775, 178.052, 0, 1, '0277676607', 'Fixed', 'Open', '2018-06-15 13:02:00', '2018-06-29 12:25:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 'Pending', 39, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Free', 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Assess', 'Firs